The paper deals with developing a new technique for dynamic topic modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing and machine learning. The paper uses probabilistic models and statistical inference techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
